Other differenceS, e. g. in procedure, and in the nature of the security to be given by the parties (Tit. 1 ι· infi), have now disappeared, and a real differs from a personal action only in the nature of the right for whose protection it is brought : the opposition is material only, not formal. It will be found that in ξ 20 inf. Justinian interposes a third class—actiones mixtae—between actions which are real and those which are personal.
